  abstract = {Providing food, energy and materials for the rising global population is
a challenge which is compounded by increased pressure on natural
resources such as land, water and fossil sources of raw materials.
Greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions from human activities have increased with
industrial development and population expansion, and it is anticipated
that resulting climate change might further limit agricultural
productivity, through changes to weather patterns and global
availability/distribution of agriculturally productive land. Growing
