volatile dimethyl sulfide. For baseline settings, the mixed layer trace
gas distribution matches sparging measurements where they are available.
However, concentrations rise to well over 10 nM in remote, unsampled
locations. Peak contributions are supported by ice grazing, mortality
and fractional melting. The model bottom layer adds substantially to a
ring maximum of reduced sulfur chemistry that may be dominant across the
